The paper discusses a novel approach to achieving efficient concurrent state access in data stream processing systems (DSPSs) on multicore processors. This involves the use of transactional semantics and two novel designs to improve scalability and parallelism. Given this focus on DSPSs and multicore processors, the most likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Other possible sub-categories include cs.DB (Databases), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.PL (Programming Languages), and cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
